OL,3,CRussian captain of ship in North Sea
OL,4,Ccrash appears in court
OL,6,FThe captain of a ship involved in a
OL,7,FNorth Sea crash 13 miles off the
OL,8,FYorkshire coast has been remanded in
OL,9,Fcustody following a 35-minute hearing.
OL,11,FFifty-nine-year-old Vladimir Motin of
OL,12,FPrimorsky, St Petersburg appeared at
OL,13,FHull Magistrates court charged with
OL,14,Fgross negligence manslaughter on
OL,15,FSaturday 15 March.
OL,17,FThe court heard how Motin's vessel the
OL,18,FSolong collided with the American
OL,19,Ftanker Stena Immaculate on Monday 10
OL,20,FMarch.
